In the case of the car accident with a fatal outcome caused by the police chief of the XXII district, the official report is now available.
The now-retired police chief of the XXII district, who killed a pedestrian in a car accident on Tuesday, was neither drunk nor under the influence of drugs, said Attila Morvai, the press spokesman for the Budapest Chief Prosecutor’s Office on Friday, after the official opinion on the case was presented.
