Finance Minister J<0xC3><0xA1>nos Veres and European Investment Bank (EIB) Vice-President Marta Gajecka signed three loan agreements in Budapest on Friday, with a total value of EUR 400 million to be invested in education, transport and environmental infrastructure and the energy sector.
