Rival Antena 3 lost 1.52 percentage points yesterday and has reported a total loss of 40.5% since January, bringing its market value to 2,193.46 million.
The market value of other listed communications companies, on the other hand, is increasing; in the case of Sogecable to 3,571 million, in the case of Prisa (publisher of the magazine Cinco D<0xC3><0xAD>as) to 2,518.53 million and in the case of Vocento to 1,779 million.
The comparison with Antena 3 can be deduced from the fact that they are two similar companies, according to Vasile.
It is still uncertain to what extent we can actually act in terms of stock exchange technology, at what price and how we can make it lucrative at the customer level.
A week ago, Telecinco announced its intention to become the first TV channel to receive more than 1000 million gross revenues from advertising revenue this year, said Guiseppe Tringali, CEO of Telecinco and Publiespa<0xC3><0xB1>a, the group’s advertising company.
If the project were to be implemented, the broadcaster would increase its advertising revenue by 3.6% compared to the 965.4 million from the previous year.
In the case of Antena 3, net sales increased by 1.6% in the first nine months of the stock market (up to 734.4 million), while net income from the television business increased by only 0.7% (630.4 million).
The main factor behind Telecinco’s better-than-expected stock market performance is the company’s high payout ratio to date: in 2006, the company led by Alejandro Echevarr<0xC3><0xAD>a generated a 100 percent dividend payout.
However, Vasile assures that the ratio after the purchase of 33% of the shares of Endemol, with Mediaset as the parent company, could still vary, even if it is too early for an official announcement.
We are committed to the official compromise to pay out at least 50% of the shares, even if we have always stated significantly more.
I hope that we can satisfy our shareholders this year, whose stock values we have already increased by buying 33% of Endemol shares.
According to the analysts, the market currently has some loss tendencies.
Lehmann Brothers recently reduced its Telecinco profit calculation for this year by 4% and for 2009 by 7%.
This is due to the reduction in the expected growth rate, which will fall from 10.5% in 2008 to 8.4% and from 5.5% to 5.1% in 2009.
This has also reduced Antena 3’s expected profit calculation for 2008 by 4.5% and for 2009 by 7.5%.
