Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of the creation of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to provide the corresponding compensation amount in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance composed of several factors, including age, gender, time of issue of the driver’s license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accidents, higher contributions are also due.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies.
The benefit attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, the insurance companies must take into account a whole series of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
We now list the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance-based but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25s encounter numerous obstacles when choosing an inexpensive insurance, such as the low driving practice and the young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance coverage to take out a comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full insurance with deductible, so that the services of a full insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract entails that the customer must pay a part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s chief representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to their own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to reduce insurance costs, so your credit will increase by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalties depend on the company and its earnings.
If the company has had a high-yielding year, it may allow itself to increase bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract, due to the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Thus, it makes the most sense to opt for a comprehensive insurance with deductible.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the fear of the beginner has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the respective person also allows.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a fully comprehensive insurance with excess (for an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which only starts at the third vehicle year.
They drive more relaxed overall and have greater purchasing power that allows them to charge a higher contribution, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with excess (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it is important to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
